WindNinja – Open‑Source Wind Modeling Software
================================================

This repository contains the source code for **WindNinja**, a public‑domain
software project developed by the Rocky Mountain Research Station (RMRS),
U.S. Forest Service.  The main code itself is released into the public
domain (see the header comment in `src/ninja/ninja.cpp`).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Third‑Party Dependencies and Their Licenses
--------------------------------------------------------------------

1. **Boost C++ Libraries**
   * Used for: date‑time handling, lexical casts, local time zones, etc.
   * License: Boost Software License 1.0
   * Full text: https://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt

2. **GDAL (Geospatial Data Abstraction Library)**
   * Used for: raster I/O, coordinate transformations, VRT creation,
     warping, and many helper utilities.
   * License: MIT‑style “X/MIT” license
   * Full text: https://gdal.org/license.html

3. **PROJ**
   * Used for: map projections and coordinate transformations (via GDAL).
   * License: MIT‑style “X/MIT” license
   * Full text: https://proj.org/about.html#license

4. **OpenMP**
   * Used for: parallel loops throughout the code base.
   * License: Apache License 2.0 (part of the LLVM/Clang runtime)
   * Full text: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

5. **Intel Math Kernel Library (MKL)**
   * Used for: BLAS‑level routines (`cblas_*`, `mkl_dcsrmv`, etc.).
   * License: Intel Simplified Software License (free for non‑commercial
     use; commercial use requires an Intel MKL license).
   * Full text: https://software.intel.com/content/www/us/en/develop/articles/intel-simplified-software-license.html

6. **TAUCS (Templated Algebraic Unstructured Solver)**
   * Used for: sparse matrix storage (`taucs_double`) and linear‑solver
     infrastructure (commented out in the current code but still present).
   * License: BSD‑style license (see `src/ninja/Preconditioner.h` for
     attribution).
   * Full text: https://github.com/jeffhammond/taucs/blob/master/LICENSE

7. **CPL (Common Portability Library) – part of GDAL**
   * Used for: configuration handling, debugging, file checks, etc.
   * License: MIT‑style “X/MIT” license (same as GDAL).

8. **Standard C++ Library**
   * Used for: containers, streams, algorithms, etc.
   * License: Implementation‑specific (e.g., GPL with the “runtime
     exception” for libstdc++, Apache 2.0 for libc++, etc.).  This
     library is provided by the compiler/runtime and does not impose
     additional restrictions on the WindNinja source.

9. **Other small utilities**
   * `jsmn` (JSON parser) – public domain / MIT‑compatible.
   * `tinyxml2` (if used elsewhere) – Zlib license.
   * Any additional header‑only helpers that ship with the source are
     covered by the same permissive licenses noted above.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Distribute
--------------------------------------------------------------------
* The core WindNinja code is in the public domain; you may use, modify,
  and redistribute it without restriction.
* When redistributing the software, you must also include the license
  texts for the third‑party components listed above.  The full license
  files can be placed in a `LICENSES/` sub‑directory, or you may embed
  the short notices (as shown here) in your distribution package.
* If you link against Intel MKL in a commercial product, ensure you
  comply with Intel’s licensing terms.

